- Python Testing framework
- Use parametrized tests for passing parameters
- Use the format `test_<what you're testing>`
- Use fixtures to create objects or deps or change the world for tests and pass in them as parameters
- fixures:
   - autouse
   - scope
   - rename
   - classes
   - plugins
   
- pytest will run all files of the form test_*.py or *_test.py in the current directory and its subdirectories
- It finds both test_ prefixed functions and Test prefixed classes
